♪You're ducking, you're a glitch, see?♪

24
00:01:30,180 --> 00:01:34,980
=See Her Again=

25
00:01:35,661 --> 00:01:37,960
=Episode 16=

26
00:01:48,660 --> 00:01:49,400
Dad,

27
00:01:52,410 --> 00:01:53,510
I finally captured

28
00:01:53,970 --> 00:01:55,350
your murderer.

29
00:01:59,940 --> 00:02:00,609
But Coroner Chen

30
00:02:00,610 --> 00:02:02,120
isn't the only person I need to capture.

31
00:02:10,260 --> 00:02:11,560
I remember you once said

32
00:02:14,180 --> 00:02:17,790
that we must behave like good people
when people are around.

33
00:02:20,050 --> 00:02:21,440
When there are no people around,

34
00:02:22,740 --> 00:02:24,640
all the more we must
behave like good people.

35
00:02:25,370 --> 00:02:29,240
(Local news, a cargo ship was caught
in a level-three fire this March.)

36
00:02:29,240 --> 00:02:32,040
(The leader of the firefighting department, Zhang Qiang
led his team aboard a ship to rescue people)

37
00:02:32,040 --> 00:02:33,960
(and was scorched by the heatwave
caused by the explosion.)

38
00:02:33,960 --> 00:02:36,160
(Even so, he still rushed into the fire
while risking his life.)

39
00:02:36,260 --> 00:02:38,040
(He rescued 12 crew-mates successfully.)

40
00:02:38,260 --> 00:02:38,929
(Today,)

41
00:02:38,930 --> 00:02:41,299
(the government awarded Zhang)

42
00:02:41,300 --> 00:02:43,089
(a commendation
to honor his courageous actions.)

43
00:02:43,090 --> 00:02:44,110
Son, look.

44
00:02:44,140 --> 00:02:45,510
Isn't Dad cool?

45
00:02:45,530 --> 00:02:47,000
He received another commendation.

46
00:02:47,330 --> 00:02:49,350
I want to be a firefighter too
when I grow up.

47
00:02:49,860 --> 00:02:51,760
- I want to receive commendations too.
- Sure.

48
00:02:51,770 --> 00:02:53,419
Tianming, you're so silly.

49
00:02:53,420 --> 00:02:54,049
You don't become

50
00:02:54,050 --> 00:02:55,560
a firefighter to receive commendations.

51
00:02:55,710 --> 00:02:57,240
You become a firefighter
to rescue people.

52
00:02:57,240 --> 00:02:58,160
Do you know something?

53
00:02:58,260 --> 00:03:00,240
We must behave like good people
when people are around.

54
00:03:00,240 --> 00:03:01,489
When there are no people around,

55
00:03:01,490 --> 00:03:03,100
all the more we must
behave like good people.

56
00:03:06,770 --> 00:03:08,070
What's the point of being good?

57
00:03:11,420 --> 00:03:13,110
Inspector Liu was a good cop.

58
00:03:14,300 --> 00:03:15,630
Why did he have to die?

59
00:03:17,210 --> 00:03:18,480
Why?

60
00:03:23,180 --> 00:03:24,350
What should I do?

61
00:03:44,650 --> 00:03:47,040
For the past few days,
I've been thinking about

62
00:03:48,860 --> 00:03:50,600
why I became a cop.

63
00:03:52,650 --> 00:03:54,910
I always believed that I became a cop

64
00:03:56,770 --> 00:03:58,830
to protect my family

65
00:04:00,210 --> 00:04:02,110
and other families.

66
00:04:05,460 --> 00:04:06,760
I became a cop

67
00:04:06,860 --> 00:04:08,560
to locate my father's murderer.

68
00:04:15,050 --> 00:04:16,360
I always felt

69
00:04:16,700 --> 00:04:18,470
that I didn't choose to become a cop.

70
00:04:19,170 --> 00:04:20,710
The job chose me instead.

71
00:04:22,530 --> 00:04:23,499
I thought

72
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:24,630
I inherited my father's gene.

73
00:04:28,460 --> 00:04:30,390
I still remember
that my father told me this.

74
00:04:31,620 --> 00:04:32,800
He said he became a coroner

75
00:04:33,330 --> 00:04:34,329
in order

76
00:04:34,330 --> 00:04:36,120
to uphold justice for innocent people.

77
00:04:42,060 --> 00:04:43,360
I truly never expected him

78
00:04:44,730 --> 00:04:46,360
to be the mastermind behind the case.

79
00:04:52,530 --> 00:04:53,630
I'm sorry, Inspector Zhang.

80
00:04:59,210 --> 00:05:00,600
It has nothing to do with you.

81
00:05:08,650 --> 00:05:09,710
Now,

82
00:05:13,170 --> 00:05:15,030
even I don't know how to continue forward.

83
00:05:18,210 --> 00:05:19,030
That's right.

84
00:05:20,530 --> 00:05:22,710
We did gather evidence of Sundess's crime.

85
00:05:23,850 --> 00:05:25,510
But the price is too huge to pay.

86
00:05:28,020 --> 00:05:29,240
Must we really do this?

87
00:05:31,940 --> 00:05:33,139
Maybe this is what cops like us

88
00:05:33,140 --> 00:05:34,270
need to face.

89
00:05:36,650 --> 00:05:38,270
There are many things
out of our control.

90
00:05:59,244 --> 00:06:04,997
♪Sunlight dissipating♪

91
00:06:07,530 --> 00:06:08,440
Stop!

92
00:06:08,700 --> 00:06:10,070
Stop! HKPD!

93
00:06:11,410 --> 00:06:12,390
Stop right there!

94
00:06:13,210 --> 00:06:14,699
This is Liu Weitao, the newcomer.

95
00:06:14,700 --> 00:06:15,510
Officer Yao.

96
00:06:18,730 --> 00:06:19,590
Officer Yao!

97
00:06:20,210 --> 00:06:20,909
Officer Yao!

98
00:06:20,910 --> 00:06:22,120
Officer Yao!

99
00:06:22,500 --> 00:06:23,397
Get up here.

100
00:06:24,650 --> 00:06:26,440
Everyone on my team is a fool.

101
00:06:26,460 --> 00:06:27,760
You're the silliest of them all.

102
00:06:28,820 --> 00:06:30,139
In the past, you were the boss.

103
00:06:30,140 --> 00:06:31,470
You're used to giving out orders.

104
00:06:31,850 --> 00:06:35,000
But today,
you have the lowest seniority among us.

105
00:06:35,060 --> 00:06:36,120
Please bear with it.

106
00:06:36,460 --> 00:06:38,120
Now, I'm telling you to close the case!

107
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:41,590
If you close the case now, you'll be letting
the true culprit get away scot-free!

108
00:06:41,650 --> 00:06:42,499
You came to 2018

109
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:43,459
from 1993.

110
00:06:43,460 --> 00:06:44,619
I helped you out every time.

111
00:06:44,620 --> 00:06:46,379
But this time, I can't.

112
00:06:46,380 --> 00:06:47,760
I'm worried that you might die.

113
00:06:48,700 --> 00:06:49,510
Officer Yao.

114
00:06:50,380 --> 00:06:52,800
You do risk your all
for your case investigations.

115
00:06:52,900 --> 00:06:54,459
I think I spent over 20 years

116
00:06:54,460 --> 00:06:55,880
just to learn 30% of your skills.

117
00:06:56,210 --> 00:06:57,270
That's more than enough.

118
00:06:57,460 --> 00:06:59,420
A person like me
actually became a chief inspector.

119
00:06:59,421 --> 00:07:01,089
♪Trying as many times♪

120
00:07:01,090 --> 00:07:02,560
I can be considered your successor now.

121
00:07:02,977 --> 00:07:06,119
♪Working tirelessly♪

122
00:07:06,120 --> 00:07:10,122
♪Braving the wind
with no tears in sight♪

123
00:07:10,123 --> 00:07:13,474
♪Replanting our roots on a small island♪

124
00:07:13,475 --> 00:07:17,466
♪Just like how the weather changes♪

125
00:07:17,467 --> 00:07:20,607
♪Working tirelessly♪

126
00:07:20,608 --> 00:07:23,600
♪In this direction♪

127
00:07:29,380 --> 00:07:30,699
(A strong low-pressure trough)

128
00:07:30,700 --> 00:07:31,920
(is approaching the harbor.)

129
00:07:31,970 --> 00:07:35,169
(The Observatory predicts
a thunderstorm warning around midnight,)

130
00:07:35,170 --> 00:07:36,939
(reaching the level of Typhoon No. 8.)

131
00:07:36,940 --> 00:07:38,390
(Citizens, please take note.)

132
00:07:51,170 --> 00:07:52,070
Were you looking for me?

133
00:07:55,820 --> 00:07:56,830
You're drenched.

134
00:07:57,530 --> 00:07:58,840
Didn't you bring an umbrella?

135
00:07:58,840 --> 00:07:59,630
It's fine.

136
00:08:00,820 --> 00:08:02,920
I wish to do something for you.

137
00:08:03,020 --> 00:08:03,760
Here.

138
00:08:18,330 --> 00:08:19,120
Here you go.

139
00:08:21,140 --> 00:08:22,200
You came here at this hour

140
00:08:22,500 --> 00:08:24,070
just to make Omelet Rice for me?

141
00:08:28,020 --> 00:08:29,030
When you were young,

142
00:08:29,090 --> 00:08:30,470
I was especially busy with work.

143
00:08:30,770 --> 00:08:33,520
I was busy catching crooks
even on the day you were born.

144
00:08:34,050 --> 00:08:35,920
I didn't have time to keep you company.

145
00:08:35,920 --> 00:08:38,000
I don't know how to make
your favorite food either.

146
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:38,680
I only know

147
00:08:38,740 --> 00:08:39,990
how to make Omelet Rice.

148
00:08:40,260 --> 00:08:41,929
Dad, I'm hungry.

149
00:08:41,930 --> 00:08:43,350
Hurry up.

150
00:08:43,860 --> 00:08:45,040
Stop urging me.

151
00:08:45,770 --> 00:08:48,200
It's piping hot.
It'll surely taste great.

152
00:08:48,930 --> 00:08:52,000
When taking Omelet Rice, you must pair it
with some ketchup to make it taste good.

153
00:08:52,620 --> 00:08:53,400
Here.

154
00:08:53,860 --> 00:08:57,830
The star represents you, Xingyao.

155
00:08:58,530 --> 00:09:01,219
The sun represents...

156
00:09:01,220 --> 00:09:03,070
The sun represents you, Dad.

157
00:09:04,140 --> 00:09:05,979
My name is Yang Guangyao.

158
00:09:05,980 --> 00:09:07,689
That's why I represent the sun. Smart girl.

159
00:09:07,690 --> 00:09:09,739
But the star and the sun

160
00:09:09,740 --> 00:09:11,259
come out at night

161
00:09:11,260 --> 00:09:12,289
and day respectively.

162
00:09:12,290 --> 00:09:14,569
They won't stay together.

163
00:09:14,570 --> 00:09:15,800
Silly girl,

164
00:09:15,810 --> 00:09:18,750
both the star and the sun
are always in the sky.

165
00:09:18,860 --> 00:09:20,470
It's just that we don't
see them sometimes.

166
00:09:21,980 --> 00:09:22,619
Eat up.

167
00:09:22,620 --> 00:09:23,800
It'll get cold. Here.

168
00:09:24,450 --> 00:09:25,870
Take a bite.

169
00:09:29,050 --> 00:09:30,440
That's a huge bite.

170
00:09:31,690 --> 00:09:32,899
This is my first time

171
00:09:32,900 --> 00:09:33,859
cooking for you.

172
00:09:33,860 --> 00:09:35,560
You should spare me some dignity.
Is it nice?

173
00:09:35,930 --> 00:09:37,110
Yeah.

174
00:09:37,500 --> 00:09:38,470
Really?

175
00:09:38,530 --> 00:09:39,920
You should eat up, then. Here.

176
00:09:52,050 --> 00:09:52,870
Wait.

177
00:09:58,140 --> 00:09:59,230
The sun

178
00:10:00,450 --> 00:10:02,280
represents Yang Guangyao.

179
00:10:04,500 --> 00:10:06,040
The star

180
00:10:07,650 --> 00:10:09,320
represents Xingyao.

181
00:10:11,500 --> 00:10:13,040
I know you might not remember

182
00:10:13,770 --> 00:10:15,710
what happened
on the night I went missing in 1993.

183
00:10:16,140 --> 00:10:17,200
I promised you

184
00:10:18,290 --> 00:10:19,680
that I would return on the second day

185
00:10:20,020 --> 00:10:21,470
and make Omelet Rice for you.

186
00:10:22,500 --> 00:10:24,689
When you wake up and open your eyes,

187
00:10:24,690 --> 00:10:26,449
you'll see me.

188
00:10:26,450 --> 00:10:27,099
You'll also see

189
00:10:27,100 --> 00:10:29,520
your favorite Omelet Rice.

190
00:10:29,810 --> 00:10:30,470
Good girl.

191
00:10:31,810 --> 00:10:35,200
I never expected that you had to wait for
more than two decades

192
00:10:36,810 --> 00:10:38,320
before I could fulfill my promise.

193
00:10:41,290 --> 00:10:42,200
I'm sorry.

194
00:10:44,020 --> 00:10:44,990
Here, eat up.

195
00:10:45,050 --> 00:10:46,320
Finish it while it's hot.

196
00:10:56,220 --> 00:10:57,280
How is it?

197
00:10:57,570 --> 00:10:58,520
Is it nice?

198
00:11:00,500 --> 00:11:01,280
Yeah.

199
00:11:11,260 --> 00:11:12,320
It's so salty.

200
00:11:12,690 --> 00:11:14,219
Stop eating it. I'll make you a new one.

201
00:11:14,220 --> 00:11:14,950
No need for that.

202
00:11:15,020 --> 00:11:16,160
I truly think it's delicious.

203
00:11:21,050 --> 00:11:22,320
You just need to practice more.

204
00:11:22,690 --> 00:11:24,870
You can make it for me again
when there's a chance.

205
00:11:29,140 --> 00:11:30,440
I might not have the chance again.

206
00:11:32,050 --> 00:11:33,590
Maybe the heavens sent me to 2018

207
00:11:33,810 --> 00:11:35,950
to investigate and solve the case.

208
00:11:38,100 --> 00:11:39,520
Now that the case is solved,

209
00:11:41,570 --> 00:11:42,990
I have a chance to return to my era.

210
00:11:47,450 --> 00:11:48,350
When?

211
00:11:49,290 --> 00:11:50,708
When Typhoon No. 8 is here.

212
00:11:50,709 --> 00:11:54,209
♪At a corner again♪

213
00:11:56,410 --> 00:11:56,997
Tonight?

214
00:11:56,998 --> 00:11:58,387
♪I don't want♪

215
00:11:59,178 --> 00:12:01,904
♪To leave your heart with emptiness♪

216
00:12:02,373 --> 00:12:04,437
♪I wish you won't throw♪

217
00:12:04,438 --> 00:12:07,594
♪The burden guilt on my shoulder♪

218
00:12:09,103 --> 00:12:11,886
♪My heart is still as water♪

219
00:12:12,409 --> 00:12:15,241
♪You need not be passionate♪

220
00:12:15,890 --> 00:12:18,575
♪Do you know♪

221
00:12:18,665 --> 00:12:22,000
♪Who is willing to return?♪

222
00:12:22,456 --> 00:12:27,512
♪Who will it be between us?♪

223
00:12:32,260 --> 00:12:35,215
♪Was it fate, love, pure♪

224
00:12:35,356 --> 00:12:38,756
♪Or an accident?♪

225
00:12:39,101 --> 00:12:42,122
♪There were tears, guilt, devotion♪

226
00:12:42,123 --> 00:12:45,394
♪And tolerance♪

227
00:12:45,395 --> 00:12:48,451
♪It was someone distant and cold♪

228
00:12:48,569 --> 00:12:51,661
♪Hidden deeply in the eyes♪

229
00:12:52,440 --> 00:12:55,466
♪There were days, nights, and fantasies♪

230
00:12:55,467 --> 00:12:58,529
♪But I couldn't wait♪

231
00:12:58,530 --> 00:13:01,710
(I don't understand why you let
daughter find you that quickly)

232
00:13:01,770 --> 00:13:03,379
(whenever you play
hide-and-seek with her.)

233
00:13:03,380 --> 00:13:06,440
(Did you see how she was panicking
when she called for me below the tree?)

234
00:13:06,930 --> 00:13:09,920
(Daughter Witnesses Mother's Death)
(My heart was broken. I couldn't stand it.)

235
00:13:09,920 --> 00:13:11,649
(I couldn't find you either.)

236
00:13:11,650 --> 00:13:13,160
(How could you bear to leave me alone?)

237
00:13:13,500 --> 00:13:14,590
(Where are you going?)

238
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:16,880
(I need to head out for a second.
I'll return soon.)

239
00:13:16,880 --> 00:13:17,710
(Will you be safe?)

240
00:13:19,450 --> 00:13:20,259
(What should we do)

241
00:13:20,260 --> 00:13:21,680
(if something happens to you?)

242
00:13:21,860 --> 00:13:24,280
(Officer Yao went missing for
over two decades. He won't just appear.)

243
00:13:24,900 --> 00:13:26,560
(It may be 25 years in your world,)

244
00:13:26,860 --> 00:13:28,830
but it was merely two days ago
in my world.

245
00:13:29,050 --> 00:13:31,019
(I must solve the case
so that I can return to my era.)

246
00:13:31,020 --> 00:13:31,830
What are you doing?

247
00:13:32,140 --> 00:13:33,040
Stop right there.

248
00:13:33,220 --> 00:13:34,920
You're a cop, not a hooligan.

249
00:13:36,500 --> 00:13:37,470
Here's your Omelet Rice.

250
00:13:37,690 --> 00:13:38,560
You don't like it?

251
00:13:38,930 --> 00:13:39,950
I'll have it later.

252
00:13:40,770 --> 00:13:42,000
What do you mean by that?

253
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:43,040
Are you a pervert?

254
00:13:43,050 --> 00:13:44,750
Why did you stick my picture with yours?

255
00:13:46,290 --> 00:13:47,800
Let me introduce someone to you.

256
00:13:48,450 --> 00:13:50,160
She's someone very important to me.

257
00:13:50,220 --> 00:13:52,110
Since you're here,
you should pay your respect.

258
00:13:52,321 --> 00:13:55,176
♪Was it fate, love, pure♪

259
00:13:55,385 --> 00:13:58,841
♪Or an accident?♪

260
00:13:59,217 --> 00:14:01,959
♪There were tears, guilt, devotion♪

261
00:14:01,960 --> 00:14:05,572
♪And tolerance♪

262
00:14:05,573 --> 00:14:08,393
♪It was someone distant and cold♪

263
00:14:08,394 --> 00:14:12,271
♪Hidden deeply in the eyes♪

264
00:14:12,272 --> 00:14:15,353
♪There were days, nights, and fantasies♪

265
00:14:15,354 --> 00:14:19,016
♪But I couldn't wait♪

266
00:14:30,050 --> 00:14:31,110
(I'm Yang Guangyao.)

267
00:14:31,500 --> 00:14:32,739
(When you were six,)

268
00:14:32,740 --> 00:14:33,926
you witnessed a car accident.

269
00:14:34,980 --> 00:14:36,560
You lost your memories.

270
00:14:37,690 --> 00:14:38,640
Xingyao.

271
00:14:39,220 --> 00:14:39,859
(In reality,)

272
00:14:39,860 --> 00:14:41,520
(you're my daughter, Xingyao.)

273
00:14:41,930 --> 00:14:44,100
(Daughter Witnesses Mother's Death)
(Do you still remember?)

274
00:14:45,447 --> 00:14:46,769
♪Was it fate, love, pure♪

275
00:14:46,770 --> 00:14:48,169
I'll take off the outer layer, then.

276
00:14:48,170 --> 00:14:48,809
That won't do.

277
00:14:48,810 --> 00:14:49,769
This is

278
